### emitDirectiveCpRestore() {#a12406a1009639db38ee6cec215d6ad2e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool MipsTargetAsmStreamer::emitDirectiveCpRestore (int Offset, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function-ref">function&#95;ref</a>&lt; unsigned()&gt; GetATReg, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smloc">SMLoc</a> IDLoc, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsubtargetinfo">MCSubtargetInfo</a> &#42; STI)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Emit a .cprestore directive.

If the offset is out of range then it will be synthesized using the assembler temporary.

GetATReg() is a callback that can be used to obtain the current assembler temporary and is only called when the assembler temporary is required. It must handle the case where no assembler temporary is available (typically by reporting an error).

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mipstargetstreamer-h/#l00287">287</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mipstargetstreamer-h">MipsTargetStreamer.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipstargetstreamer-cpp/#l00699">699</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipstargetstreamer-cpp">MipsTargetStreamer.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
